'''Walsall F.C. Reserves and Youth''' are the reserve and youth team for [[League One]] club [[Walsall F.C.|Walsall]].

The reserve team play in the [[The Football Combination|Football Combination Central Division]].  Walsall Reserves play their home games at the [[Bescott Stadium]], [[Walsall]] and they also at the occasionally play at [[The Lamb Ground]], home of [[Tamworth F.C.|Tamworth]].

The youth team play in the [[Football League Youth Alliance|Youth Alliance North West Conference]] and are only for players below 18. They play their home games at academy base at the Birmingham County FA Ground, Ray Hall Lane, Great Barr.

==Walsall F.C. reserve team==
The Reserve team currently play in the [[The Football Combination|The Football Combination Central Division]]. The side is used by [[Football League One|League One]] club [[Walsall F.C.|Walsall]] to take youngsters from the youth up a step closer to the first-team, however it can also be used as a team to allow first-team players to gain match fitness after an injury or suspension. The Walsall reserves enjoyed success in 2001â02 when they won the league and cup double.

